%N A397162 Decimal expansion of the large face angle, in radians, of a canonical (dual-uniform) tetragonal trapezohedron.
%C A397162 The tetragonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the square antiprism.
%C A397162 Its faces are kites with one acute angle (A397161) and three obtuse angles (this constant).
%H A397162 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397162/b397162.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397162 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/TetragonalTrapezohedron.html">Tetragonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397162 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Square_antitegum">Square antitegum</a>.
%H A397162 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397162 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetragonal_trapezohedron">Tetragonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397162 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A397162 Equals arccos((1 - sqrt(2))/2) = arccos((1 - A002193)/2).
%F A397162 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.2071... is the smallest root of 4*x^2 - 4*x - 1.
%e A397162 1.779413017104045226092537750623845834346797686860...
